BinoBi – Commercial Source Available License
Version 1.0 – 2025

Copyright (c) 2025 SVEN HERRMANN. All rights reserved.

1. Definitions

"Software" means the command line tool `bino`, including all source code,
binary files, configuration files, documentation and any other related
materials provided by SVEN HERRMANN.

"Internal Use" means use of the Software solely within a single
organization for its own internal purposes, without third parties (such as
customers or external partners) receiving payment for, or commercially
benefiting from, the use of the Software or the results generated with it.

"Commercial Use" means any use of the Software or its results that directly
or indirectly aims at generating revenue or forms part of a paid product or
service.

2. Granted Rights

2.1. Source Code Access  
You may read and inspect the source code of the Software and study it for the
purposes of understanding, evaluation and internal use.

2.2. Internal Use  
You may use the Software within your own organization free of charge to create
internal analyses, evaluations or reports (for example business reports,
PDF reports), provided that such results are used exclusively for internal
purposes.

3. Restrictions

Unless you have obtained an individual, written commercial license from
SVEN HERRMANN, you are expressly PROHIBITED from doing the following:

3.1. Commercial use of the Software  
You may not use the Software for commercial purposes. In particular, you may
not:

    a) offer the Software as part of a paid product or service,
    b) integrate the Software into a SaaS, cloud or platform solution that is
       made available to third parties (whether for payment or as part of a
       commercial offering),
    c) use the Software as the technical basis for a competing product or any
       other commercial tool.

3.2. Commercial use of results produced by the Software  
You may not use results produced by the Software (for example reports, PDFs,
analyses) in order to:

    a) sell these results to third parties or offer them for payment,
    b) create such results as part of paid services for clients (for example
       as a reporting provider, agency or consultant),
    c) use these results as part of a commercial product or service.

Only internal use of results within your own organization is permitted.

3.3. Distribution and sublicensing  
Without the prior written consent of SVEN HERRMANN, you may not:

    a) copy, publish or distribute the Software to third parties,
    b) distribute, rent, lease or otherwise make the Software available,
    c) sublicense or grant usage rights to third parties.

3.4. Modification and derivative works  
You may not modify or edit the Software or create derivative works that you
make available to third parties, distribute or use commercially, unless you
have a written agreement with SVEN HERRMANN that expressly permits this.

Internal adaptations for your own use are permitted only if the adapted
Software is used exclusively internally and neither the adapted Software nor
its results are used commercially within the meaning of Sections 3.1 or 3.2.

4. Individual Commercial License

If you wish to use the Software or its results commercially (for example to
provide services to clients, to build a commercial product or a SaaS
solution), please contact:

    SVEN HERRMANN
    Oskar-Eckert-Ste. 6
    97250 Erlabrunn
    GERMANY

    sven@bino.bi

to negotiate an individual commercial license.

5. No entitlement to an open source license

SVEN HERRMANN may decide in the future to release the Software in whole or in
part under an open source license. However, there is no legal entitlement to
such a change or to it taking place at any specific time.

6. Disclaimer of Warranty

THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT ANY EXPRESS OR IMPLIED WARRANTY,
INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A
PARTICULAR PURPOSE AND NON-INFRINGEMENT OF THIRD-PARTY RIGHTS. THE ENTIRE
RISK AS TO THE QUALITY AND PERFORMANCE OF THE SOFTWARE LIES WITH YOU.

7. Limitation of Liability

IN NO EVENT SHALL SVEN HERRMANN BE LIABLE TO YOU OR ANY THIRD PARTY FOR ANY
DAMAGES (INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO LOST PROFITS, BUSINESS INTERRUPTION,
LOSS OF BUSINESS INFORMATION OR OTHER ECONOMIC LOSS) ARISING OUT OF THE USE
OF OR INABILITY TO USE THE SOFTWARE, EVEN IF SVEN HERRMANN HAS BEEN ADVISED
OF THE POSSIBILITY OF SUCH DAMAGES.

8. Term and Termination

This license becomes effective upon the first download, installation or use
of the Software and remains in effect until terminated.

SVEN HERRMANN may terminate this license without notice if you violate any of
the terms of this license. In the event of termination, you must:

    a) immediately cease using the Software, and
